    <prp:code/>
    <prp:abstract>We propose deep Band 8 observations for our luminous spectroscopically-confirmed galaxy at z=7.308. We target an [OIII]88um line that is the strongest FIR line for metal poor galaxies revealed by recent Herschel programs. An [OIII] line is from HII regions, which is a good indicator of oxygen abundance. This program will complement on-going ALMA observations for z~7 galaxies, targeting a [CII]158um line of PDRs that poorly determines metallicity. Our goals are to detect an [OIII] line of our galaxy, and estimate oxygen abundance at the highest redshift ever obtained. Even if the [OIII] line is not detected, it will place a 3sigma-upper limit of Z/Zsun&lt;~0.07 that reveals a very metal poor nature. With stellar mass and SFR already given by HST and Spitzer observations, we will investigate a deviation from the fundamental mass-metallicity relation and test whether the z=7.3 galaxy is experiencing a non-equilibrium mode of star formation. Due to the atmospheric transmission, high-sensitivity [OIII] observations are limited to z&gt;~7. This challenging experiment is enabled by our z=7.3 galaxy, observable from ALMA, that is identified by a powerful combination of Subaru and Keck surveys.</prp:abstract>
